data.description: Escape the hustle and bustle of the city and experience the country living this Monroe home has to offer! 2555 Old Athens Highway is situated on a level 1.27 acres and just a short drive to the shopping and restaurants of downtown Monroe and just 30 minutes to UGA. From subway tile backsplash to shiplap to custom board and batten, you will fall in love with the upgraded features and accents. Granite countertops don the kitchen and beautiful LVP flooring is featured throughout the home. The kitchen overlooks the living room, providing a partially open floor plan. You'll love sharing memories and meals in your dining room. Separate from the common areas, each bedroom offers a quiet retreat. One of the secondary bedrooms is great for a potential office or reading room. All of the bedrooms offer plenty of space, but the primary bedroom is incomparable. Just off of the living room, you will find a hallway that leads you right to the oversized primary bedroom with en suite and a large walk-in closet. Not only will it comfortably house your king size bedroom set, but a sectional sofa and large tv could easily fit to make it feel like a true suite. In addition to the many cosmetic updates, the roof has recently been replaced and the backyard houses a 12x36 workshop/shed and a 35x15 pole barn - both with electricity and the pole barn is plumbed and ready for your RV or camper! Enjoy grilling on the back porch or entertain guests and light the fire pit on your sizable patio; host a corn hole tournament or even buy a few chickens. This beautiful home coupled with its outdoor space offers all of the charm and endless possibilities for you to enjoy small town living. All that's missing is you!
